All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary 
    Class Description
    AntennaCommand
    Represents a command sent from a controller to a device (or passed from a device to another device) Commands have no timestamp, only a type and arguments in Data.
    AntennaCommand.Type
    Types of Commands stored by their respective protocol code and length of arguments accepted in bytes
    AntennaController
    Controls a device by running scripts and outputting to log
    AntennaDevice
    Interface representing an AntennaDevice Essentially functions as a two way event bus with listeners
    AntennaDevice.Listener
    A listener for the event (registered with addEventListener) that can be used with lambdas
    AntennaDeviceBase
    Thread safe event listener implementation of AntennaDevice
    AntennaEvent
    Represents a events sent from a device to a listener (or passed from a device to another device) Events must have a timeStamp in milliseconds from a baseTime (or epoch)
    AntennaEvent.Type
    Types of Events stored by their respective protocol code and length of arguments accepted in bytes
    AntennaScript
    An abstract, runnable representation of a script
    AntennaScriptInstruction
    A single instruction in a script.
    Hex
    Utility class for displaying bytes as hexadecimal codes
    MockAntennaDevice
    Mocks a real Antenna device for testing
    NetworkAntennaDevice
    A device that communicates over a TCP socket
    NetworkAntennaServer
    A server that wraps an AntennaDevice to communicate over a TCP socket
    Units
    Utility class for converting between 4 byte integer (unit) positions and degrees
